{
  "doc_id": "FC-LS",
  "source_pdf": "/Users/zwy/毕设/V7/data/raw/FC-LS.pdf",
  "page": 159,
  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0002",
      "text": " 140",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0003",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        57.65,
        114.34,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0004",
      "text": "F_RJT Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID of",
      "bbox": [
        122.37,
        57.65,
        540.09,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0005",
      "text": "the PLOGI.  The Fabric has rejected the PLOGI request.  The reason code contained in the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        69.65,
        539.97,
        80.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0006",
      "text": "Payload determines the Nx_Port’s action.  If the reason code is \"Invalid D_ID\",  N_Port Login is",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        81.65,
        540.02,
        92.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0007",
      "text": "not possible with the addressed Nx_Port.  The Nx_Port may attempt Login with other destina-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        93.65,
        540.01,
        104.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0008",
      "text": "tion Nx_Ports.  For other reason codes, the Nx_Port should respond according to the code.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        105.64,
        524.6,
        116.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0009",
      "text": "d) P_BSY Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        130.97,
        539.98,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0010",
      "text": "of the PLOGI.  The destination Nx_Port is busy.  The Nx_Port may retry the PLOGI again later.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        142.96,
        539.96,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0011",
      "text": "e) P_RJT Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI.  The D_ID shall be the S_ID of",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        166.96,
        540.16,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0012",
      "text": "the PLOGI.  The reason code contained in the Payload determines the Nx_Port’s action.  If the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        178.96,
        540.05,
        190.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0013",
      "text": "reason code is \"Class not supported\", the Nx_Port may attempt PLOGI in a different class.  For",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        190.96,
        540.01,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0014",
      "text": "other reason codes, the Nx_Port should responded according to the code.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        202.96,
        449.54,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0015",
      "text": "f)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        226.96,
        112.13,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0016",
      "text": "PLOGI Sequence.  The D_ID is the N_Port_ID of receiving Nx_Port.  The S_ID is the",
      "bbox": [
        122.38,
        226.96,
        540.08,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0017",
      "text": "N_Port_ID of the originating Nx_Port.  The OX_ID is as assigned by the originating Nx_Port.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        238.96,
        540.02,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0018",
      "text": "The Payload shall include a 64-bit N_Port_Name and 64-bit Node_Name of the Nx_Port origi-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        250.96,
        539.97,
        262.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0019",
      "text": "nating the PLOGI.  This indicates a collision with N_Port Login from the destination Nx_Port.  If",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        262.96,
        540.05,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0020",
      "text": "the received N_Port_Name is less than the receiving Nx_Port's N_Port_Name, the Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        274.96,
        540.01,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0021",
      "text": "sends LS_RJT to the originating Nx_Port with reason code \"Command already in progress\".  If",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        286.96,
        540.16,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0022",
      "text": "the received N_Port_Name is greater than its N_Port_Name, the Nx_Port processes the re-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        298.96,
        540.07,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 8,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0023",
      "text": "ceived PLOGI.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        310.96,
        187.4,
        322.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 9,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0024",
      "text": "g) LS_RJT Sequence with OX_ID equal to the OX_ID of the PLOGI.  The D_ID of the LS_ACC",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        334.96,
        539.99,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0025",
      "text": "shall be the N_Port_ID of the destination Nx_Port.  The reason code contained in the Payload",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        346.96,
        540.05,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0026",
      "text": "determines the Nx_Port’s action.  The Nx_Port may alter the Service Parameters based on the",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        358.96,
        540.07,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0027",
      "text": "reason code and originate a new PLOGI.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        370.96,
        303.46,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0028",
      "text": "h) No Response may indicate a delivery error, e.g., error on the physical transport.  The Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        394.96,
        540.05,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0029",
      "text": "shall perform error recovery per FC-FS-2.  The Nx_Port may originate a new PLOGI after re-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        406.96,
        540.08,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0030",
      "text": "covery.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        418.96,
        154.57,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0031",
      "text": "i)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        442.96,
        111.56,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0032",
      "text": "If the received N_Port_Name is equal to its N_Port_Name, then the Nx_Port is connected to it-",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        442.96,
        539.95,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0033",
      "text": "self and this case is outside the scope of this standard.",
      "bbox": [
        122.4,
        454.96,
        364.6,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0034",
      "text": "6.3.2.4  N_Port Login - No Fabric present",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.96,
        288.67,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0035",
      "text": "This procedure is based on the Nx_Port discovering the Fabric is not present during an attempted",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        502.96,
        539.88,
        514.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0036",
      "text": "Fabric Login. (see 6.2.2.3) The destination N_Port explicit Login procedure requires transmission of a",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        514.96,
        540.01,
        526.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0037",
      "text": "PLOGI Link Service Sequence in a new Exchange.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        526.96,
        321.53,
        538.07
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0038",
      "text": "Only one Nx_Port in the point-to-point connection is required to transmit a PLOGI.  If the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        539.99,
        562.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0039",
      "text": "N_Port_Names are exchanged during Fabric Login, the Nx_Port with the highest N_Port_Name shall",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        540.01,
        574.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0040",
      "text": "transmit the PLOGI.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        184.35,
        586.07
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0041",
      "text": "If either Nx_Port does not have access the N_Port_Name of the connected Nx_Port, it may send a",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        598.96,
        539.97,
        610.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0042",
      "text": "PLOGI.  The processing requirements for responses received after transmitting a PLOGI resolves",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        610.96,
        540.04,
        622.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0043",
      "text": "the condition of both Nx_Ports transmitting PLOGI.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        622.96,
        320.4,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0044",
      "text": "An Nx_Port in a point-to-point configuration transmits PLOGI within a new Exchange.  The S_ID shall",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        647.02,
        539.97,
        658.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0045",
      "text": "be different than the D_ID.  The Payload of this Sequence contains the Service Parameters,",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        659.02,
        539.97,
        670.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0046",
      "text": "N_Port_Name, and Node_Name of the Nx_Port originating the PLOGI Sequence.  The N_Port Ser-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        671.02,
        540.02,
        682.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0047",
      "text": "vice Parameters are as specified for in 6.6.  The applicability of the Service Parameters to N_Port Lo-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        683.02,
        540.03,
        694.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p159_s0048",
      "text": "gin are given in tables 150 and 155.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        695.02,
        254.37,
        706.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    }
  ],
  "asset_ids": []
}